
[1]diatonic

   DIATONIC, a. [Gr., by or through, sound.] Ascending or descending, as
   in sound, or from sound to sound. This epithet is given to a scale or
   gammut, to intervals of a certain kind, or to music composed of these
   intervals; as a diatonic series; a diatonic interval; diatonic melody
   or harmony. It is applied to ordinary music, containing only the two
   greater and lesser tones, and the greater semitone.
